[src:code-generation-templates/template-metaprogramming] The C++20 standard brought C++ programmers a new tool for meta template programming, concepts.
[src:code-generation-templates/template-metaprogramming] Concepts allow programmers to specify requirements for the type, to make instantiation of template possible.
[src:code-generation-templates/template-metaprogramming] The compiler looks for a template with the concept that has the highest requirements.
[src:code-generation-templates/template-metaprogramming] Here is an example of the famous Fizz buzz problem solved with Template Meta Programming.
[src:code-generation-templates/template-metaprogramming] Compile-time versus execution-time tradeoffs get visible if a great deal of template metaprogramming is used.
